WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Exodus chapter 16, Exodus chapter number 16.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:08.000
I'll read the first four verses by way of introduction

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:10.000
and we'll dig into the text this evening.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:13.000
Exodus chapter number 16.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:16.000
If you were here last week on Wednesday evening,

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
you'll recall that we examined part of Exodus chapter 9.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:22.000
When we examined part of that passage,

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:25.000
it was dealing with the seventh plague.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:28.000
And we talked about, as we looked at that portion of Scripture,

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:30.000
and we asked ourselves this question,

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:34.000
considered the thought, how do we respond to God?

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:37.000
God is faithful to give us truth,

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:39.000
and we find that even in that text of Scripture,

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:41.000
God gave truth to Moses.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:45.000
He then delivers it to the people with regard to that seventh plague.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:48.000
And it was very clear, man or beast that's in the field,

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:50.000
they're going to die when the hail comes,

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:53.000
and therefore, here's what you do, bring them in.

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:56.000
And we said that there were some that took heed,

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:58.000
there were others that regarded not the word of the Lord,

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:00.000
and of course, what happened?

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:02.000
Well, tomorrow, like God said, the hail came,

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:04.000
and any that were in the field died.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.000
And we asked ourselves the question,

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:08.000
why would they respond that way?

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:10.000
And then we have to look ourselves in the mirror and say,

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:13.000
why do we respond sometimes in disobedience

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:16.000
to the clear instruction that God gives?

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
And we looked at that, dealing really with the Egyptians

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:22.000
and their response last week in chapter 9.

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:24.000
Look at chapter 16.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:26.000
You may already be familiar with the text

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:28.000
just by mentioning it's Exodus 16.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:30.000
It's the record that God gives us of manna.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:33.000
And notice the Bible says in verse number 1,

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:35.000
And they took their journey from Elam,

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:37.000
and all the congregation of the children of Israel

00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:39.000
came unto the wilderness of Sin,

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:41.000
which is between Elam and Sinai,

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:43.000
on the fifteenth day, the second month,

00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:45.000
after their departing out of the land of Egypt.

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:47.000
And the whole congregation of the children of Israel

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:51.000
murmured against Moses and Aaron in the wilderness.

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:55.000
Does that please God? No.

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:58.000
Verse 3, And the children of Israel said unto them,

00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:01.000
Would to God we had died by the hand of the Lord

00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:04.000
in the land of Egypt, when we sat by the flesh pots,

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:06.000
and when we did eat bread to the full,

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:09.000
for ye have brought us forth into this wilderness

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:12.000
to kill this whole assembly with hunger.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:14.000
Then said the Lord unto Moses,

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:18.000
Behold, I will rain bread from heaven for you,

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:20.000
when the people shall go out and gather

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:23.000
a certain rate every day, that I may prove them

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:27.000
whether they will walk in my law or no.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:29.000
As we look at this text of Scripture,

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:31.000
we'll go down through verse number 28 this evening.

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:33.000
I've simply titled from verse number 4,

00:02:33.000 --> 00:02:36.000
I will rain bread from heaven.

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:38.000
Tonight, as we look at this portion of Scripture,

00:02:38.000 --> 00:02:41.000
we'll see how God's people responded to His instruction.

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:44.000
I believe this evening, and you've often heard me say it,

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:47.000
that our behavior really reveals what we believe.

00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:51.000
We can say all day long that we believe X, Y, Z,

00:02:51.000 --> 00:02:55.000
but the proof of what we truly believe is evidenced,

00:02:55.000 --> 00:02:58.000
is demonstrated through how we behave,

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:00.000
through the things that we do.

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:03.000
We find that in the text of Scripture that is before us,

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:06.000
that God gives the record of this provision,

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:08.000
this manna from heaven.

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:10.000
Of course, we understand the Lord Jesus Christ,

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:13.000
and we won't have time this evening or Wednesday night

00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:17.000
to deal with the truth of Jesus as being the bread of heaven,

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:20.000
the bread of life, and all of that.

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:22.000
But as we look contextually at Exodus 16

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:25.000
and really kind of continue the thought from last week

00:03:25.000 --> 00:03:27.000
with how do we respond to God,

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:29.000
but then looking in this passage,

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:31.000
not at the Egyptians,

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:33.000
and we did ask the question last week,

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:35.000
this wasn't the first plague last week,

00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:37.000
it was the seventh plague.

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:40.000
So they'd already witnessed the hand and power of God,

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:42.000
and yet, though it was the seventh plague,

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:44.000
there were some that still regarded not.

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:47.000
They didn't believe that it was actually going to happen.

00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:50.000
Now we're looking at the children of Israel in Exodus 16,

00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:52.000
and I want you to consider just a few things

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:54.000
by way of introduction this evening

00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:57.000
when you consider all that they had witnessed firsthand.

00:03:57.000 --> 00:04:01.000
They not only had the opportunity to see the ten plagues

00:04:01.000 --> 00:04:06.000
and to experience the power of God through the plagues,

00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:08.000
we understand that as we study the plagues

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:11.000
that there were even a portion of those plagues

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:13.000
where the Egyptians were impacted,

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:15.000
but the children of Israel were not impacted,

00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:17.000
and God made that distinction,

00:04:17.000 --> 00:04:20.000
and he said that he would on certain plagues,

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:23.000
and they had the opportunity to experience that.

00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:26.000
Of course, we understand that they left Egypt

00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:28.000
and they got to the Red Sea,

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:30.000
and what happens when they're at the Red Sea?

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:32.000
Well, very similar to what we read

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:34.000
in the text of Scripture by way of introduction

00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:36.000
in Exodus chapter 16,

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:37.000
here they say,

00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:39.000
you've brought us forth into the wilderness to kill us.

00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:41.000
They had the same idea there.

00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:45.000
It wasn't so much with hunger in that text of Scripture

00:04:45.000 --> 00:04:47.000
as much as it was that there was the sea before them

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:49.000
and the Egyptians behind them,

00:04:49.000 --> 00:04:52.000
but they still had and reached the same conclusion.

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:54.000
You brought us here that we would die.

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:57.000
There were not enough graves in Egypt, et cetera,

00:04:57.000 --> 00:04:59.000
and so we find that the children of Israel,

00:04:59.000 --> 00:05:01.000
they experienced being in that place,

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:05.000
and Pihahirath is where God led them to,

00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:08.000
and then God miraculously parted the Red Sea,

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:10.000
and they witnessed that firsthand.

00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:12.000
Not only did they see it with their eye,

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:15.000
but every one of them literally had to walk through

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:17.000
on dry ground.

00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:18.000
Amen?

00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:22.000
So they saw it, but they physically experienced it.

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:25.000
They walked through with walls of water on either side.

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:27.000
Can you imagine?

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:29.000
To see the power of God.

00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:32.000
And then God closed up the waters,

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:35.000
and the Egyptians were destroyed.

00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:37.000
And they were singing in Exodus 15

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:40.000
of all of God's greatness and His goodness

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:41.000
and all that He did,

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:43.000
and by the time you get to the end of chapter 15,

00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:45.000
they find themselves in a place called Marah

00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:47.000
where the water is bitter,

00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:48.000
and what do they do?

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:50.000
They immediately complain.

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:51.000
And what does God do?

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:53.000
Well, He instructs Moses,

00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:55.000
and He tells them take that wood

00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:57.000
and throw it in that tree,

00:05:57.000 --> 00:05:59.000
and the waters were made sweet,

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:00.000
and they were sustained.

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:02.000
Again, they got to see this.

00:06:02.000 --> 00:06:04.000
And so as we look at Exodus chapter number 16

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:06.000
and we come to the place that we're at,

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:08.000
I want you to first see, number one,

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:09.000
the miraculous provision,

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:11.000
and we look here at the text

00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:13.000
and we begin to see this miraculous provision,

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:16.000
and again, we've just went through

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:19.000
all that these people had experienced.

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:21.000
Can I say to you this evening

00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:23.000
that we as the people of God,

00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:25.000
we today not only have the opportunity

00:06:25.000 --> 00:06:28.000
to read the entire canon of Scripture,

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:31.000
but we've been able to see God work

00:06:31.000 --> 00:06:33.000
in our lives firsthand as well.

00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:35.000
We sang this evening about God hearing

00:06:35.000 --> 00:06:36.000
and answering prayer.

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:38.000
I hope tonight you've experienced

00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:40.000
God answering prayer in your life.

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:43.000
I hope tonight you can look at your life

00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:45.000
and you can see God's hand at work

00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:50.000
and you can rejoice in what God has done.

00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:54.000
We find that these children of Israel

00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:56.000
that are here, this generation,

00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:58.000
they've experienced all of this

00:06:58.000 --> 00:07:00.000
wonderful work of God.

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:01.000
They've seen it firsthand.

00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:03.000
They've experienced it,

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:05.000
but yet they come to a place

00:07:05.000 --> 00:07:08.000
and they're hungry and they're murmuring.

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:09.000
The Bible says in verse number two

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:11.000
that the whole congregation

00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:12.000
of the children of Israel

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:14.000
murmured against Moses and Aaron

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:15.000
in the wilderness.

00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:16.000
It wasn't just a part of them.

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:18.000
It was all of them.

00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:19.000
The whole congregation.

00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:21.000
Can you imagine?

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:22.000
Oftentimes, when we talk about

00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:23.000
spiritual leadership,

00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:25.000
we'll reference the difficulties

00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:27.000
in which Moses dealt with

00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:29.000
on leading the children of Israel

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:31.000
and God adequately and appropriately

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:32.000
referred to the children of Israel

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:34.000
as being stiff-necked people,

00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:38.000
and certainly they were.

00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:41.000
Sometimes we can be stiff-necked too.

00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:42.000
Amen?

00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:43.000
Sometimes when we look at

00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:44.000
the children of Israel,

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:45.000
we're real quick to be able

00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:47.000
to criticize them

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:48.000
and to be able to look at

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:49.000
what they're doing and say,

00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:50.000
how could they,

00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:53.000
but then we stop short

00:07:53.000 --> 00:07:54.000
of actually looking in the mirror

00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:56.000
and saying, how does my behavior

00:07:56.000 --> 00:08:00.000
actually mirror what they did?

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:01.000
And we look at the text of Scripture

00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:03.000
and we see their complaining,

00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:04.000
we see their murmuring,

00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:06.000
and we find that God,

00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:09.000
listen, our God is so gracious.

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:11.000
Isn't He so gracious?

00:08:11.000 --> 00:08:12.000
The Bible says that

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:13.000
the children of Israel,

00:08:13.000 --> 00:08:14.000
they complained in verse two

00:08:14.000 --> 00:08:15.000
and verse three,

00:08:15.000 --> 00:08:18.000
and they, in verse two,

00:08:18.000 --> 00:08:19.000
it just simply summarizes

00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:20.000
the fact that they murmured

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:21.000
against Moses and Aaron

00:08:21.000 --> 00:08:22.000
in the wilderness,

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:23.000
and verse three kind of explains

00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:25.000
in detail what they said,

00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:26.000
and they were thinking back

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:28.000
to what they had

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:29.000
while they were in Egypt.

00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:30.000
They quickly forgot

00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:32.000
how they were crying out

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:33.000
while they were in Egypt,

00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:35.000
were they not?

00:08:35.000 --> 00:08:36.000
They were crying out for deliverance.

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:37.000
What did God say

00:08:37.000 --> 00:08:38.000
when He showed up

00:08:38.000 --> 00:08:39.000
and talked to Moses?

00:08:39.000 --> 00:08:42.000
He said, I've heard their cry.

00:08:42.000 --> 00:08:43.000
Amen?

00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:45.000
So what do they remember in Egypt?

00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:47.000
They only remember the good things,

00:08:47.000 --> 00:08:49.000
quote unquote.

00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:51.000
And so they're thinking,

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:52.000
they're saying, oh,

00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:54.000
that we were back there,

00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:55.000
and had they died

00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:56.000
in the land of Egypt

00:08:56.000 --> 00:08:57.000
when we sat by the flesh pots

00:08:57.000 --> 00:08:59.000
and did eat bread to the full.

00:08:59.000 --> 00:09:00.000
And then they're talking

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:01.000
about this hunger.

00:09:01.000 --> 00:09:02.000
So what does God say

00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:03.000
in verse number four?

00:09:03.000 --> 00:09:06.000
Notice the miraculous provision.

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:07.000
God makes a promise

00:09:07.000 --> 00:09:08.000
in verse number four.

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:10.000
Then said the Lord unto Moses,

00:09:10.000 --> 00:09:13.000
Behold, I will reign bread

00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:17.000
from heaven for you.

00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:19.000
Now, I want you to just consider

00:09:19.000 --> 00:09:20.000
for a moment

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:22.000
Moses hearing these words.

00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:24.000
I will reign bread

00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:27.000
from heaven for you.

00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:28.000
And to begin to think

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:29.000
for just a moment,

00:09:29.000 --> 00:09:31.000
we read and we understand,

00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:32.000
and we've been taught

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:34.000
maybe for many different times

00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:35.000
as we've walked

00:09:35.000 --> 00:09:37.000
this Christian journey.

00:09:37.000 --> 00:09:39.000
We understand manna.

00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:40.000
We understand what God did.

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:42.000
But can you imagine Moses

00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:43.000
hearing these words from God

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:44.000
when God says,

00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:46.000
I'm going to reign bread

00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:48.000
from heaven for you.

00:09:48.000 --> 00:09:49.000
We could ask ourselves

00:09:49.000 --> 00:09:50.000
the question,

00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:51.000
how's that going to work?

00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:52.000
How's that going to happen?

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:53.000
What's the process?

00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:54.000
And we find that God's

00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:55.000
making this promise.

00:09:55.000 --> 00:09:56.000
The reality is that

00:09:56.000 --> 00:09:57.000
God can do whatever

00:09:57.000 --> 00:09:58.000
he wants to do

00:09:58.000 --> 00:09:59.000
however he wants to do it.

00:09:59.000 --> 00:10:03.440
The only thing that God is bound by is his word,

00:10:03.440 --> 00:10:05.539
and he's the one that gave his word,

00:10:05.539 --> 00:10:09.739
so he has put things within his word that would bind him,

00:10:09.739 --> 00:10:10.579
but that's it.

00:10:10.579 --> 00:10:13.279
We find that the unbelief of God's people,

00:10:13.279 --> 00:10:15.139
often on the case of the children of Israel,

00:10:15.139 --> 00:10:16.819
limited the Holy One of Israel,

00:10:16.819 --> 00:10:18.059
but we find that God says,

00:10:18.059 --> 00:10:21.120
"'I will reign bread from heaven for you.

00:10:21.120 --> 00:10:22.700
"'The people shall go out

00:10:22.700 --> 00:10:24.559
"'and gather a certain rate every day.

00:10:24.559 --> 00:10:26.399
"'Notice this, that I may prove them

00:10:26.399 --> 00:10:29.739
"'whether they will walk in my law or no.'"

00:10:29.739 --> 00:10:32.020
And so we find this miraculous provision

00:10:32.020 --> 00:10:35.159
that God makes this promise to Moses

00:10:35.159 --> 00:10:37.659
and then to be delivered to the children of Israel,

00:10:37.659 --> 00:10:40.180
and that God is going to do this thing.

00:10:40.180 --> 00:10:43.900
We understand that it ended up lasting for 40 years.

00:10:43.900 --> 00:10:45.419
Can you imagine?

00:10:45.419 --> 00:10:47.340
Again, this is something that most of us

00:10:47.340 --> 00:10:48.659
on a Wednesday night crowd,

00:10:48.659 --> 00:10:49.939
we know about the manna.

00:10:49.939 --> 00:10:51.540
We're like, yeah, yeah, manna.

00:10:51.540 --> 00:10:53.900
This is miraculous.

00:10:53.900 --> 00:10:56.680
God is providing for his people.

00:10:56.680 --> 00:10:59.080
So we see the miraculous provision.

00:10:59.080 --> 00:11:00.080
I want you to see number two,

00:11:00.080 --> 00:11:02.159
the meticulous process.

00:11:02.159 --> 00:11:03.239
We find in the New Testament,

00:11:03.239 --> 00:11:04.239
in the book of 1 Corinthians,

00:11:04.239 --> 00:11:06.000
that God tells us that our God,

00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:07.879
he says that all things are to be done decently

00:11:07.879 --> 00:11:08.720
and in order.

00:11:08.720 --> 00:11:10.559
Our God is a God of order.

00:11:10.559 --> 00:11:12.680
Our God is a God of detail.

00:11:13.860 --> 00:11:14.699
If you read,

00:11:14.699 --> 00:11:16.599
if you continue reading through the book of Exodus

00:11:16.599 --> 00:11:18.660
and you begin to read about the tabernacle

00:11:18.660 --> 00:11:22.160
and all of the explicit detail that is provided

00:11:22.180 --> 00:11:25.819
with regard to the construction of the tabernacle,

00:11:25.819 --> 00:11:27.819
I mean, it is extremely detailed.

00:11:27.819 --> 00:11:29.660
You go throughout the scriptures

00:11:29.660 --> 00:11:32.379
and you find that our God is a God of detail.

00:11:32.379 --> 00:11:36.779
I mentioned on Sunday evening about worship,

00:11:36.779 --> 00:11:38.620
and I said all that's called worship today

00:11:38.620 --> 00:11:39.739
is not really worship,

00:11:39.739 --> 00:11:41.980
and man oftentimes thinks they can approach God

00:11:41.980 --> 00:11:43.139
on their terms,

00:11:43.139 --> 00:11:46.099
but yet God has meticulously explained to us

00:11:46.099 --> 00:11:48.819
in his word how we're to approach him.

00:11:48.819 --> 00:11:50.379
And here in the text of scripture,

00:11:50.400 --> 00:11:52.480
we find that there's a meticulous process

00:11:52.480 --> 00:11:53.720
that they're to follow.

00:11:53.720 --> 00:11:54.919
In verses four and five,

00:11:54.919 --> 00:11:56.959
God gives a very general overview,

00:11:56.959 --> 00:11:58.559
a summary if you will,

00:11:58.559 --> 00:12:01.519
and then provides greater details in verses eight through 19.

00:12:01.519 --> 00:12:03.319
Notice in verse five and six,

00:12:03.319 --> 00:12:04.160
it says,

00:12:04.160 --> 00:12:06.220
and it shall come to pass that on the sixth day,

00:12:06.220 --> 00:12:09.119
they shall prepare that which they bring in,

00:12:09.119 --> 00:12:11.800
and it shall be twice as much as they gather daily.

00:12:11.800 --> 00:12:14.479
And so we notice that in verse number four,

00:12:14.479 --> 00:12:16.960
it said that they should gather a certain rate every day

00:12:16.960 --> 00:12:18.119
that I may prove them

00:12:18.119 --> 00:12:19.800
whether they will walk in my law or no,

00:12:19.800 --> 00:12:22.360
and it shall come to pass, verse five,

00:12:22.360 --> 00:12:24.100
that on the sixth day,

00:12:24.100 --> 00:12:26.419
they shall prepare that which they bring in,

00:12:26.419 --> 00:12:29.820
and it shall be twice as much as they gather daily.

00:12:29.820 --> 00:12:31.500
And so then in verses six and seven,

00:12:31.500 --> 00:12:32.619
the Bible says that Moses and Aaron

00:12:32.619 --> 00:12:33.860
said unto all the children of Israel,

00:12:33.860 --> 00:12:34.699
it even,

00:12:34.699 --> 00:12:37.179
then you shall know that the Lord hath brought you out

00:12:37.179 --> 00:12:38.380
from the land of Egypt,

00:12:38.380 --> 00:12:39.339
and in the morning,

00:12:39.339 --> 00:12:41.300
then you shall see the glory of the Lord,

00:12:41.300 --> 00:12:44.139
for that he heareth your murmuring against the Lord,

00:12:44.139 --> 00:12:46.559
and what are we that ye murmur against us?

00:12:46.559 --> 00:12:49.460
I want you to just on a side note this evening,

00:12:49.460 --> 00:12:51.279
understand that in verse number seven,

00:12:51.279 --> 00:12:53.360
God heard their murmuring,

00:12:53.360 --> 00:12:54.759
and that in verse number two,

00:12:54.759 --> 00:12:56.399
the Bible says that the whole congregation

00:12:56.399 --> 00:12:58.960
of the children of Israel murmured against who?

00:12:58.960 --> 00:13:00.000
Moses and Aaron,

00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:02.440
but what does Moses say in verse number seven,

00:13:02.440 --> 00:13:04.039
that he, God, the Lord,

00:13:04.039 --> 00:13:07.100
he heareth your murmuring against the Lord?

00:13:08.440 --> 00:13:09.500
Against the Lord.

00:13:11.479 --> 00:13:12.679
We find that it says,

00:13:12.679 --> 00:13:15.080
and what are we that ye murmur against us?

00:13:15.080 --> 00:13:17.160
Moses understood his place,

00:13:17.160 --> 00:13:19.419
and as he led the children of Israel,

00:13:20.259 --> 00:13:22.479
he was simply following God's leadership.

00:13:22.479 --> 00:13:24.279
And we come to verse number seven,

00:13:24.279 --> 00:13:25.500
it says in the morning,

00:13:25.500 --> 00:13:27.199
then you shall see the glory of the Lord,

00:13:27.199 --> 00:13:28.020
or verse eight, excuse me,

00:13:28.020 --> 00:13:28.860
and Moses said,

00:13:28.860 --> 00:13:31.559
this shall be when the Lord shall give you in the evening,

00:13:31.559 --> 00:13:32.479
flesh to eat,

00:13:32.479 --> 00:13:33.320
and in the morning,

00:13:33.320 --> 00:13:34.199
bread to the full,

00:13:34.199 --> 00:13:36.039
for that the Lord heareth your murmurings,

00:13:36.039 --> 00:13:37.440
which you murmur against him,

00:13:37.440 --> 00:13:38.279
and what are we?

00:13:38.279 --> 00:13:39.539
Your murmurings are not against us,

00:13:39.539 --> 00:13:40.800
but against the Lord.

00:13:40.800 --> 00:13:44.679
So in verses nine through 19,

00:13:44.679 --> 00:13:47.320
we see that these details are being provided

00:13:47.339 --> 00:13:50.020
for this meticulous process.

00:13:50.020 --> 00:13:51.899
Again, this is a familiar passage of scripture,

00:13:51.899 --> 00:13:53.139
many of us would know this,

00:13:53.139 --> 00:13:54.740
we could answer the questions,

00:13:54.740 --> 00:13:55.880
but I want you to look at it,

00:13:55.880 --> 00:13:56.720
in verse nine, it says,

00:13:56.720 --> 00:13:57.979
and Moses spake unto Aaron,

00:13:57.979 --> 00:14:01.059
say unto all the congregation of the children of Israel,

00:14:01.059 --> 00:14:03.300
come near before the Lord,

00:14:03.300 --> 00:14:04.820
for he hath heard your murmurings.

00:14:04.820 --> 00:14:05.979
And it came to pass,

00:14:05.979 --> 00:14:07.979
as Aaron spake unto the whole congregation

00:14:07.979 --> 00:14:09.380
of the children of Israel,

00:14:09.380 --> 00:14:10.740
that they looked toward the wilderness,

00:14:10.740 --> 00:14:12.860
and behold, the glory of the Lord appeared in the cloud,

00:14:12.860 --> 00:14:15.179
and the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

00:14:15.179 --> 00:14:17.059
verse 12, I have heard the murmuring

00:14:17.640 --> 00:14:18.480
of the children of Israel.

00:14:18.480 --> 00:14:19.640
Speak unto them, saying,

00:14:19.640 --> 00:14:21.799
at even ye shall eat flesh,

00:14:21.799 --> 00:14:24.480
and in the morning ye shall be filled with bread.

00:14:24.480 --> 00:14:25.320
And notice this,

00:14:25.320 --> 00:14:29.600
and ye shall know that I am the Lord your God.

00:14:29.600 --> 00:14:31.160
In verse 13, it came to pass

00:14:31.160 --> 00:14:33.500
that at even the quails came up and covered the camp,

00:14:33.500 --> 00:14:35.679
and in the morning the dew lay round about the host,

00:14:35.679 --> 00:14:37.839
and when the dew that lay was gone up,

00:14:37.839 --> 00:14:39.640
behold, upon the face of the wilderness

00:14:39.640 --> 00:14:41.359
there lay a small round thing,

00:14:41.359 --> 00:14:44.320
as small as the hoarfrost on the ground.

00:14:44.320 --> 00:14:46.959
When the children of Israel saw it,

00:14:47.899 --> 00:14:49.619
they said one to another, it is manna,

00:14:49.619 --> 00:14:51.579
for they wist not what it was.

00:14:51.579 --> 00:14:52.739
And Moses said unto them,

00:14:52.739 --> 00:14:57.739
this is the bread which the Lord hath given you to eat.

00:14:58.059 --> 00:15:01.380
This was the provision, the promise of verse number four,

00:15:01.380 --> 00:15:03.040
I will reign bread from heaven for you.

00:15:03.040 --> 00:15:04.619
This is the fulfillment.

00:15:04.619 --> 00:15:08.179
This is the bread which the Lord hath given you to eat.

00:15:08.179 --> 00:15:09.820
And then notice the details.

00:15:09.820 --> 00:15:12.239
This is the thing which the Lord hath commanded.

00:15:12.239 --> 00:15:14.339
So notice, in verse number 16,

00:15:14.339 --> 00:15:16.059
Moses is making it very plain.

00:15:16.059 --> 00:15:18.079
This is not my commandment to you.

00:15:18.079 --> 00:15:20.920
This is what God has commanded.

00:15:20.920 --> 00:15:22.959
And it's always important for us to understand

00:15:22.959 --> 00:15:25.519
that Moses, he was a faithful minister.

00:15:25.519 --> 00:15:27.519
Moses had been entrusted of the Lord

00:15:27.519 --> 00:15:31.720
to take a message from God and to deliver to the people,

00:15:31.720 --> 00:15:33.760
and Moses was faithful to do that.

00:15:33.760 --> 00:15:37.559
We find that here, that as Moses begins to instruct them

00:15:37.559 --> 00:15:39.440
and to provide them with the details,

00:15:39.440 --> 00:15:40.899
he says that this is the thing

00:15:40.899 --> 00:15:42.480
which the Lord hath commanded.

00:15:42.480 --> 00:15:45.959
Notice verse 16, gather of it, of the manna,

00:15:46.660 --> 00:15:48.980
according to his eating, an omer for every man,

00:15:48.980 --> 00:15:51.299
according to the number of your persons,

00:15:51.299 --> 00:15:55.140
take ye every man for them which are in his tents.

00:15:55.140 --> 00:15:57.700
The children of Israel did so,

00:15:57.700 --> 00:16:00.339
and gathered some more, some less,

00:16:00.339 --> 00:16:02.019
and they did meet it with an omer.

00:16:02.019 --> 00:16:04.619
Then he that gathered much had nothing over,

00:16:04.619 --> 00:16:06.959
and he that gathered little had no lack.

00:16:06.959 --> 00:16:10.820
They gathered every man according to his eating.

00:16:10.820 --> 00:16:13.700
And so we find that Moses provides additional instruction

00:16:13.700 --> 00:16:14.540
in verse number 19.

00:16:14.540 --> 00:16:16.760
Notice very plainly, and Moses said,

00:16:16.760 --> 00:16:20.799
let no man leave of it till the morning.

00:16:20.799 --> 00:16:23.519
So we find that on day one through day five,

00:16:23.519 --> 00:16:24.839
they were to collect,

00:16:24.839 --> 00:16:28.600
they were to go gather enough manna for each day.

00:16:28.600 --> 00:16:30.480
We find that he makes it very clear

00:16:30.480 --> 00:16:32.880
that they're to keep none until the morning.

00:16:32.880 --> 00:16:36.760
In verse 19, let no man leave of it till the morning.

00:16:36.760 --> 00:16:38.959
And so we find, again, is there anything complicated

00:16:38.959 --> 00:16:41.040
about these instructions?

00:16:41.040 --> 00:16:42.559
It's a meticulous process.

00:16:42.559 --> 00:16:44.359
We find that our God is a God of order.

00:16:45.179 --> 00:16:46.220
Our God is a God of details.

00:16:46.220 --> 00:16:49.420
And God says to the children of Israel through Moses,

00:16:49.420 --> 00:16:53.179
here's the process, here's how you're to go out and gather.

00:16:53.179 --> 00:16:56.299
Day one through day five, here are the instructions.

00:16:56.299 --> 00:16:59.140
And so we find that in verse number,

00:16:59.140 --> 00:17:00.220
skip down if you will,

00:17:00.220 --> 00:17:04.019
and we'll look here at verse number 20.

00:17:04.019 --> 00:17:04.859
Look at 20.

00:17:04.859 --> 00:17:06.980
Notwithstanding, they hearken not unto Moses,

00:17:06.980 --> 00:17:08.700
but some of them left of it until the morning,

00:17:08.700 --> 00:17:10.380
and it bred worms and stank,

00:17:10.380 --> 00:17:12.459
and Moses was wroth with them.

00:17:12.480 --> 00:17:14.559
And we notice in verse number 21,

00:17:14.559 --> 00:17:17.239
and they gathered it every morning,

00:17:17.239 --> 00:17:18.880
every man according to his eating.

00:17:18.880 --> 00:17:20.760
And when the sun waxed hot, it melted,

00:17:20.760 --> 00:17:23.660
and it came to pass that on the sixth day,

00:17:23.660 --> 00:17:25.640
they gathered twice as much bread,

00:17:25.640 --> 00:17:26.920
two omers for one man,

00:17:26.920 --> 00:17:29.679
and all the rulers of the congregation came and told Moses.

00:17:29.679 --> 00:17:31.200
So notice in verse 22,

00:17:31.200 --> 00:17:34.239
this is doing exactly what God had said in verse number five,

00:17:34.239 --> 00:17:36.619
and it shall come to pass that on the sixth day,

00:17:36.619 --> 00:17:38.519
they shall prepare that which they bring in,

00:17:38.519 --> 00:17:41.440
and it shall be twice as much as they gather daily.

00:17:41.440 --> 00:17:43.700
But there were some, the rulers of the congregation,

00:17:43.700 --> 00:17:46.700
they came to Moses and they said in verse number 23,

00:17:46.700 --> 00:17:48.859
this is that, and he said unto them,

00:17:48.859 --> 00:17:50.179
so they brought the report,

00:17:50.179 --> 00:17:52.660
this is that which the Lord hath said.

00:17:52.660 --> 00:17:56.079
Tomorrow is the rest of the holy Sabbath unto the Lord.

00:17:56.079 --> 00:17:57.959
Bake that which you will bake today,

00:17:57.959 --> 00:18:00.500
and seethe that you will seethe,

00:18:00.500 --> 00:18:02.260
and that which remaineth over,

00:18:02.260 --> 00:18:07.260
lay up for you to be kept until the morning.

00:18:07.299 --> 00:18:09.859
And they laid it up till the morning as Moses bade,

00:18:09.859 --> 00:18:14.079
and it did not stink, neither was there any worm therein.

00:18:14.079 --> 00:18:15.679
And so we find that as we would look

00:18:15.679 --> 00:18:17.279
at the meticulous process,

00:18:17.279 --> 00:18:19.239
and we'd understand these details,

00:18:19.239 --> 00:18:20.920
and we'd understand that day six

00:18:20.920 --> 00:18:23.600
is different than days one through five.

00:18:23.600 --> 00:18:25.519
And I want you to consider with me

00:18:25.519 --> 00:18:28.239
that as God gives this instruction,

00:18:28.239 --> 00:18:31.440
and I want you to consider being the children of Israel here

00:18:31.440 --> 00:18:33.159
in receiving this instruction.

00:18:33.159 --> 00:18:34.659
Again, there's nothing confusing,

00:18:34.659 --> 00:18:36.320
there's nothing complicated,

00:18:36.320 --> 00:18:38.640
but we find that on days one through five,

00:18:38.640 --> 00:18:40.859
if I gather enough just for today,

00:18:40.859 --> 00:18:42.539
I'm not supposed to store it up,

00:18:42.539 --> 00:18:44.840
I'm not supposed to let it stay until morning,

00:18:44.840 --> 00:18:46.099
but then on day six,

00:18:46.099 --> 00:18:48.940
I'm supposed to go out and gather twice as much,

00:18:48.940 --> 00:18:51.840
and I am supposed to keep it until the morning

00:18:51.840 --> 00:18:54.760
because I'm not gonna go gather on the Sabbath.

00:18:54.760 --> 00:18:57.260
And again, if we lean on our own understanding,

00:18:57.260 --> 00:19:01.559
I want you to consider those that did gather extra

00:19:01.559 --> 00:19:02.780
and left it until the morning,

00:19:02.780 --> 00:19:03.619
what happened?

00:19:03.619 --> 00:19:05.659
Well, it bred worms and it stank.

00:19:05.659 --> 00:19:07.500
That's what the Bible tells us.

00:19:07.500 --> 00:19:08.559
So all of a sudden,

00:19:08.559 --> 00:19:10.640
we can start leaning on our own understanding and saying,

00:19:10.640 --> 00:19:13.000
well, if it happened on day three,

00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:15.919
then how is it not gonna happen on day six?

00:19:17.599 --> 00:19:18.440
Right?

00:19:18.440 --> 00:19:21.799
We begin to insert our own thoughts

00:19:21.799 --> 00:19:25.440
and our own reasoning and our own logic into,

00:19:25.440 --> 00:19:29.719
and we try to go through the process of,

00:19:29.719 --> 00:19:31.940
well, I know God said this, but.

00:19:34.159 --> 00:19:36.400
I know this is what God said,

00:19:36.859 --> 00:19:39.059
but you don't understand my situation.

00:19:39.059 --> 00:19:40.219
I know this is what God said,

00:19:40.219 --> 00:19:42.219
but you don't understand my circumstances.

00:19:42.219 --> 00:19:43.500
I know this is what God said,

00:19:43.500 --> 00:19:47.500
but we're in 2025 and they said I had to do this

00:19:47.500 --> 00:19:49.000
and this responsibility.

00:19:49.960 --> 00:19:52.419
You understand what I'm saying this evening?

00:19:52.419 --> 00:19:54.380
And so we come to the portion of scripture

00:19:54.380 --> 00:19:56.580
and we find that on day six,

00:19:56.580 --> 00:19:58.539
they were to have enough for two days.

00:19:58.539 --> 00:20:03.539
And God had made it clear that they were to store it up and that it would not spoil and

00:20:03.539 --> 00:20:07.499
they would have provision for that seventh day.

00:20:07.499 --> 00:20:11.859
God knew what they needed and God would provide what they needed.

00:20:11.859 --> 00:20:16.739
But they would not go out and gather on the Sabbath.

00:20:16.739 --> 00:20:20.419
And so we find that there's a meticulous process that's laid out.

00:20:20.419 --> 00:20:27.099
Sometimes when we go to the Bible, we look at the scriptures and say, they're so detailed.

00:20:27.099 --> 00:20:29.699
And I think that's a good thing.

00:20:29.699 --> 00:20:36.579
Because God provides for us as his people, what he expects for us to do.

00:20:36.579 --> 00:20:38.899
What it is that pleases him.

00:20:38.899 --> 00:20:42.819
You know, have you ever gotten some instructions and you've said, these things are not worth

00:20:42.819 --> 00:20:45.559
the ink and paper that they used?

00:20:45.559 --> 00:20:47.139
Because they're so vague.

00:20:47.139 --> 00:20:48.139
I don't know.

00:20:48.139 --> 00:20:53.699
I mean, I've taken instructions before and jokingly with Joseph, I've taken the instructions

00:20:53.939 --> 00:20:57.139
And I've pulled them open something like this and I'll hold them like, well, maybe it's

00:20:57.139 --> 00:20:58.139
supposed to be this way.

00:20:58.139 --> 00:21:01.059
Like, cause it's just, it makes no sense.

00:21:01.059 --> 00:21:07.659
And the reality is that when we come to the word of God, God gives us clarity.

00:21:07.659 --> 00:21:09.499
God provides us with the details.

00:21:09.499 --> 00:21:14.819
There's no, nothing vague within the text of scripture that we're looking at here in

00:21:14.819 --> 00:21:16.199
Exodus 16.

00:21:16.199 --> 00:21:18.179
And we find this meticulous process.

00:21:18.179 --> 00:21:23.419
We could ask ourselves the question, could God have given them enough on day one that

00:21:23.419 --> 00:21:25.179
they could have had it for the entire week?

00:21:25.179 --> 00:21:26.779
Sure he could.

00:21:26.779 --> 00:21:30.099
Could he have given it enough on day one that they could have stored it up for an entire

00:21:30.099 --> 00:21:31.099
month?

00:21:31.099 --> 00:21:32.099
Sure.

00:21:32.099 --> 00:21:38.539
God could do whatever he wants, but he gave them a particular process and it was meticulous

00:21:38.539 --> 00:21:41.499
and it was, it was detailed.

00:21:41.499 --> 00:21:48.059
And God, as we look at the text of scripture, he was doing two things.

00:21:48.059 --> 00:21:53.179
We notice in verse number 12, at the end of the verse, he says, and you shall know that

00:21:53.939 --> 00:21:56.979
I am the Lord your God.

00:21:56.979 --> 00:22:02.219
So God is helping to develop his people.

00:22:02.219 --> 00:22:05.019
He's building their faith.

00:22:05.019 --> 00:22:10.939
He's helping them to understand that he is able to provide for them.

00:22:10.939 --> 00:22:12.899
He is able to meet their needs.

00:22:12.899 --> 00:22:15.059
